HEADWORD: Homophony
<hw>Ho*moph"o*ny</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/: cf. F.
<ets>homophonie</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Sameness of
sound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Sameness of sound;
unison.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Plain harmony, as opposed to
<xex>polyphony</xex>. See <er>Homophonous</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Homophylic</ent>⟦br⟧
